items.title: Is the Trump Administration About to Cause AbbVie, Eli Lilly, and Johnson & Johnson Stocks to Crash?
items.description: President Trump recently warned big drugmakers that a pharmaceutical "tariff wall" is coming.  Investors often view Pharmaceutical stocks as safe havens during periods of market turbulence.  Indeed, shares of the three biggest pharmaceutical companies based on market cap -- AbbVie (NYSE: ABBV), Eli Lilly (NYSE: LLY), and Johnson & Johnson (NYSE: JNJ) -- have all delivered solid gains so far this year, while the major market indexes have fallen.
